In Popular Culture[edit]

Man's Favorite Sport? (1964) features Rock Hudson as a fishing expert at Abercrombie and Fitch, then in its pre-1977 existence as an elite outfitter of sporting and excursion goods, and featuring its expensive fishing rods, fishing boats, and tents

