Abercrombie & Fitch Company (NYSE:ANF) Stock Rating Upgraded by Vetr Inc
Xavier Trudeau
Juillet 23, 2017



Part












The stock's quarterly performance represents pessimistic momentum of -14.13 percent. The brokerage now has a $12.64 price target on the apparel retailer's stock.
A number of other analysts have also recently issued reports on the company. Finally, FBR & Co reissued a "hold" rating and set a $13.00 price target on shares of Abercrombie & Fitch in a research note on Friday, May 26th. William Blair restated an "outperform" rating on shares of Abercrombie & Fitch in a research note on Monday. TheStreet downgraded shares of Abercrombie & Fitch from a "c-" rating to a "d+" rating in a report on Thursday, June 15th.Wunderlich downgraded the stock and lowered the price target on May 11 changing the price objective from $30.00 to $12.00 and changing the rating from "Hold" to "Sell". Sell-side research firms now have a consensus one year price target of $12.00 on the stock according to First Call.Abercrombie & Fitch Company has a market cap of 650.23M and has seen an average daily volume of 4129460 over the past three months.Market Capitalization can be thought of as the overall price to buy the company. Looking at the stock's movement on the chart, Abercrombie & Fitch Co. recorded a 52-week high of $23.29. The stock is trading $12.15 its 50-day moving average by 2.53%.Abercrombie & Fitch (NYSE:ANF) last announced its earnings results on Thursday, May 25th. The consensus mean EPS for the current quarter is at $-0.33 derived from a total of 18 estimates from the analysts who have weighed in on projected earnings.Currently Abercrombie & Fitch Company (NYSE:ANF)'s shares owned by insiders are 0.4%, whereas shares owned by institutional owners are 0%. The business had revenue of $661.10 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $651.25 million. For the current year, analysts are predicting earnings of $-0.31 per share according to First Call. Adjusted sales, which excludes the impact from Victory Motorcycles net sales for the second quarter of 2017, were $1.36 billion compared to $1.13 billion in the prior year period. On average, analysts anticipate that Abercrombie & Fitch Company will post ($0.31) EPS for the current year.COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: This news story was published by StockNewsTimes and is the sole property of of StockNewsTimes. If you are viewing this piece on another publication, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of US and global copyright & trademark legislation. The original version of this piece can be accessed at https://www.thestockobserver.com/2017/07/22/abercrombie-fitch-company-nyseanf-stock-rating-upgraded-by-vetr-inc-updated.html. Credit Agricole S A bought a new stake in Abercrombie & Fitch during the fourth quarter worth approximately $120,000. Teachers Retirement System of The State of Kentucky increased its stake in shares of Abercrombie & Fitch by 38.7% in the fourth quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 5,686,072 shares of the apparel retailer's stock worth $67,836,000 after buying an additional 42,429 shares during the period. Finally, Gotham Asset Management LLC increased its stake in Abercrombie & Fitch by 145.5% in the first quarter. State Street Corp now owns 3,297,400 shares of the apparel retailer's stock worth $39,340,000 after buying an additional 326,288 shares during the period. Highbridge Capital Management LLC bought a new stake in shares of Abercrombie & Fitch during the fourth quarter worth about $674,000.Abercrombie & Fitch Co is a specialty retailer who primarily sells its products through store and direct-to-consumer operations, as well as through various wholesale, franchise and licensing arrangements. The Company offers an array of apparel products, including knit tops, woven shirts, graphic t-shirts, fleece, sweaters, jeans, woven trousers, shorts, outerwear, dresses, intimates and swimwear, and personal care products and accessories for men, women and kids under the Abercrombie & Fitch, abercrombie kids, Hollister and Gilly Hicks brands.

 




