Abercrombie & Fitch signs deal to carry full-range of products on
Jay Anderson
July 23, 2017



Share












Following the stock price relative to moving averages may offer enhanced perspective on stock performance.
On November 23 the stock rating was downgraded from "Hold" to "Sell" in a report from Deutsche Bank.Other analysts have also issued reports about the company. Royal Bank Of Canada reissued a "sell" rating and issued a $12.00 price target on shares of Abercrombie & Fitch in a report on Monday, April 10th. FBR & Co reiterated a "hold" rating and set a $13.00 target price on shares of Abercrombie & Fitch in a report on Friday, May 26th. Ten investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, thirteen have assigned a hold rating, three have assigned a buy rating and one has assigned a strong buy rating to the company. The stock has an average rating of "Hold" and a consensus target price of $13.85.Abercrombie & Fitch Company (NYSE:ANF) has been given a $13.00 price target by analysts at Jefferies Group LLC in a note issued to investors on Monday, July 10th. The stock closed the most recent session at $9.56 after seeing 3315807 shares trade hands.Shares of the company are trading at $9.56 barely below the 50 day moving average of $11.68 and marginally under the 200 day moving average of $11.93.The firm's market capitalization is $654.31 million. For the current year the company's revenue estimates are $3.27 Billion compared to low analyst estimates of $3.19 Billion and high estimates of $3.33 Billion according to the prediction of 17 analysts. However a year ago for the same quarter the company has reported $-0.25 EPS. The firm had revenue of $661.10 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $651.25 million.

